UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407678900581
AB  - The problem considered here is the ‘first-order’ identification of linear models, i.e., the identification of the coefficients of the variables appearing in the model. A general approach is proposed and very simple results are stated in this general context. A geometric interpretation of this approach is given. Classical results in this area are shown to be special cases of these general results.
